"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"Esquites is an off-the-cob version of elote--the sweet, smoky, Mexican corn served from street vendors. This is best made with fresh sweet corn, but frozen can work when you're looking for that perfect comfort dish in off-season months. The flavors of this dish are versatile--enjoy as a side with any Mexican or BBQ fare such as enchiladas, tacos, grilled/roasted chicken, BBQ pork, or burgers. This is best served at room temperature.\\n\\n## Directions\\n\\nInstructions Checklist\\n\\n* Step 1\\n\\n  Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add corn and epazote. Cook, stirring frequently, until cooked to your preference, about 6 minutes. Remove from heat.\\n* Step 2\\n\\n  Combine crema and lemon juice in a bowl; season with salt. Mix crema into the hot corn and transfer mixture to a serving dish. Let cool to room temperature.\\n* Step 3\\n\\n  Sprinkle Cotija cheese and chipotle powder on top of corn and serve with lime wedges.[ \\n ](https://www.allrecipes.com/cook/5698242/)\",\"timestamp\":1640336614,\"title\":\"Esquites\"},\"digest\":\"2LAoAV_SjAtrnpB9DMO81DIujOEN-2Y1vZENWhLKXT8\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xf38f40C5cEaC554D4c7c37128cc0C062810776B4\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"o2byo86R3Lk3DRCa_0Juy-Rn5C6RN4iNh0GICO6h03Q\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"8ikO38YWPi_RABNilzjCeVCJxFL1vnTny80oCrqTlIA\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"USHcKmnb9pv251MeE7bTOUpqR5PsC4LLPvP-iZtuGrD7n1-52iItLHex97Xj9LHIrUPJSGMnog-TaZRqMTMbyg\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xfe0f31575913602b7c499f43bca46ec19d8d7c3b5a2de4fb08d4149b8981d38a7d014ddb2facb4c7b6465f6f18ffa1f3311a1f72cd7ebc3b3c9bc5dca115c7d31b\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"o2byo86R3Lk3DRCa_0Juy-Rn5C6RN4iNh0GICO6h03Q\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"8ikO38YW